floors.lesson:
While loops are used to execute code numerous times while a given expression or value evaluates to true. You can construct a while statement by using the following syntax. The code within the 'while' block will execute so long as myBoolean is true. 

	while (myBoolean) {
		// your code
	}. 
It is very important to be careful when using loops, as infinitely executing loops will likely cause problems for a program. As such, it is important to make sure that any variables within a while statement are being updated as needed within the while block.

